result.name: Victoria Harbour Supreme

reviews.text: A Chinese restaurant serving mainly seafood cuisines. Conveniently located within the commercial complex of Taipo Station, the restaurant has the advantage of being the only Chinese restaurant in that area and hence free of any keen competition from its peers. The standard of food is above average and the braised lobster with noodle is a must try. Prices are reasonable and hence the restaurant is full most of the time especially during the weekends.

My in-laws seem fond of the place and one cannot be hard on it provided it delivers consistent food that people enjoy.  Expect a wait if not early, moreover, if uninitiated the food can be very heavy and oily which is the correct format for a teahouse.

The food is good, service is fast, and as expected it's very very busy.
Convenient location near the Tai Po Market station. Dim sum quality is average but the service and environment are satisfactory.

Fair quality food.
Fair quality service and hygiene.

Free parking available,  ask for receipt when check.
One CLP EV Quick Charge available at carpark.
I am biased as this is a common place for our family get together. Super convenient location. Great food.

A Chinese restaurant serving mainly seafood cuisines. Conveniently located within the commercial complex of Taipo Station, the restaurant has the advantage of being the only Chinese restaurant in that area and hence free of any keen competition from its peers. The standard of food is above average and the braised lobster with noodle is a must try. Prices are reasonable and hence the restaurant is full most of the time especially during the weekends.

食物一般， 侍應趕住收碟， 如果唔係一大班人食飯， 真係唔會去 。
想食好嘅食物，千祈唔好去！

My in-laws seem fond of the place and one cannot be hard on it provided it delivers consistent food that people enjoy.  Expect a wait if not early, moreover, if uninitiated the food can be very heavy and oily which is the correct format for a teahouse.

The food is good, service is fast, and as expected it's very very busy.

result.name: Uptown Plaza

reviews.text: Nice shopping mall, just relatively small 😅😭
Shopping mall at the Tai Po Market train station. Get almost all the stuff you need for ADL here.

This is a smaller mall which is also connected to the MTR and is worth it if you're nearby but not for sight seeing or so forth.  If you ever are needing something quick you can get off at the Tai PO Market station and come here for the usual fair found at such connected plazas.
A convenience place still renuvating some part of it.
a small shopping centre with basic shops and restaurants, nice customer service.
